images.description: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Whisk the eggs in a bowl.
Fry the eggs until fully cooked.
Cook potatoes in boiling water for 15 minutes.
Add garlic and cook for 2 minutes.
Let the meat rest for 10 minutes.
Chill in the refrigerator for 1 hour.
Serve with a garnish of choice.
Stir in the chocolate until melted.
Pour into cups and serve hot.
Let the dough rise for 1 hour.
Season the meat with salt and pepper.
Sear the meat on high heat.
Roast the meat in the oven for 20 minutes.
Drizzle the sauce over the meat.
Add wet ingredients and mix until combined.
Pour batter into a baking dish.
Preheat the grill to high heat.
Mix the herbs with olive oil.
Drizzle the herb oil over the vegetables.
Roll out the dough to 1/4 inch thick.
Cut out shapes using a cookie cutter.
Place the shapes on a baking sheet.
Decorate the cookies after they cool.
Pour the dressing over the salad and toss to coat.
